    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="432"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d432">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Choate</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 14, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 383.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my dispatch No. 381, of 11th
                    instant, I have the honor to inclose herewith the copy of a telegram<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d432fn2">Circular telegram printed ante, <ref target="#pg_301">p.
                            301</ref>.</note> which I received from you on the 12th instant, and
                    which I lost no time in communicating to Her Majesty’s Government.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Joseph H. Choate.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
